                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small;">Fol. 6va: Record concerning the gathering of the monks to prohibit the selling of the monastery's books. </span></p><q xml:lang="gez"><div style="margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:&#10;normal"><span style="font-size: small;"><span unicode="">Fol. 6va: </span></span><span style="font-size: large;"><span>&#4845;&#4708;&#4617;&#4961; </span><span>&#4632;</span><span>&#4637;&#4613;</span><span>&#4651;</span><span>&#4757;&#4961; &#4808;&#4789;&#4622;&#4633;&#4961; &#4779;&#4613;&#4755;&#4725;&#4961; &#4808;&#4618;&#4675;&#4813;&#4757;&#4725;&#4961; &#4824;&#4848;&#4709;&#4648;&#4961; &#4851;&#4638;&#4961;&#160;&#4720;&#4875;&#4706;&#4774;&#4633;&#4961; &#4813;&#4661;&#4720;&#4961; &#4708;&#4720;&#4961; &#4781;&#4653;&#4661;&#4722;&#4843;&#4757;&#4962; &#4773;&#4661;&#4632;&#4961; &#4656;&#4637;&#4817;&#4961; &#4776;&#4632;&#4961; &#4644;&#4901;&#4814;&#4757;&#4961; &#4616;&#4709;&#4825;&#4739;&#4725;&#4961; &#4632;&#4923;&#4629;&#4941;&#4725;&#4961; &#4725;&#4779;&#4725;&#4961; &#4768;&#4709;&#4851;&#4757;&#4961; &#4656;&#4709;&#4773;&#4961; &#4768;&#4813;&#4650;&#4854;&#4633;&#4961; &#4773;&#4637;&#4848;&#4709;&#4653;&#4962; &#4808;&#4704;&#4773;&#4757;&#4720;&#4829;&#4961; &#4845;&#4708;&#4617;&#4961; &#4768;&#4640;&#4653;&#4752;&#4961; &#4808;&#4768;&#4813;&#4872;&#4829;&#4752;&#4961; &#4704;&#4675;&#4621;&#4752;&#4961; &#4776;&#4632;&#4961; &#4770;&#4725;&#4931;&#4773;&#4961; &#4827;&#4722;&#4961; &#4632;&#4925;&#4624;&#4941;&#4961; &#4773;&#4637;&#4768;&#4757;&#4672;&#4920;&#4961; &#4708;&#4720;&#4961; &#4781;&#4653;&#4661;&#4722;&#4843;&#4757;&#4962;</span><span> &#4808;&#4779;&#4821;&#4704;&#4961; &#4845;&#4708;&#4617;&#4961; &#4616;&#4827;&#4722;&#4961; &#4632;&#4925;&#4624;&#4941;&#4961; &#4824;&#4640;&#4648;&#4675;&#4961; &#4808;&#4936;&#4624;&#4675;&#4961; &#4808;&#4768;&#4813;&#4648;&#4851;&#4961; &#4773;&#4637;&#4848;&#4709;&#4653;&#4961; &#4808;&#4768;&#4813;&#4933;&#4768;&#4961; &#4773;&#4637;&#4768;&#4757;&#4672;&#4920;&#4961; &#4708;&#4720;&#4961; &#4781;&#4653;&#4661;&#4722;&#4843;&#4757;&#4961; &#4824;&#4773;&#4757;&#4704;&#4616;&#4961; &#4616;&#4653;&#4773;&#4845;&#4961; &#4808;&#4768;&#4757;&#4709;&#4710;&#4961; &#4704;&#4813;&#4661;&#4724;&#4723;&#4961; &#4845;&#4777;&#4757;&#4961; &#4813;&#4873;&#4824;&#4961; &#4704;&#4645;&#4621;&#4899;&#4752;&#4961; &#4675;&#4622;&#4633;&#4961; &#4616;&#4916;&#4901;&#4654;&#4661;&#4961; &#4808;&#4915;&#4813;&#4622;&#4661;&#4961; &#4768;&#4875;&#4821;&#4829;&#4722;&#4752;&#4962; &#4808;&#4704;&#4675;&#4617;&#4961; &#4616;&#4768;&#4648;&#4875;&#4810;&#4961; &#4768;&#4705;&#4752;&#4961; &#4808;&#4704;&#4675;&#4616;&#4961; </span>&#4773;&#4877;&#4829;&#4773;&#4725;&#4752;&#4961; &#4677;&#4853;&#4661;&#4725;&#4961; &#4853;&#4757;&#4877;&#4621;&#4961; &#4635;&#4653;&#4843;&#4637;&#4961; <span>&#4773;&#4633;&#4961; &#4616;&#4632;&#4853;&#4739;&#4754;&#4752;&#4962;</span></span></div></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"><p><span style="font-size: small;">Fol. 6va: Gathered in the church, teachers and all priest and masters of D&#228;br&#228; Dammo said (the following) because they heard that foolish men sold many old books having taken them down from the mountain. Because of this they said, "We condemn and excommunicate with our word that this book may not leave the gate of the church". And furthermore they said, "The one who stole this book or erased (its text) or took it down from the mountain or brought it out from the gate of the church except for looking or reading inside shall be excommunicated by the authority of the word of our lords Peter and Paul and by the word of our father &#704;Ar&#228;gawi and by the word of our Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, mother of our Saviour". </span></p></q>
                           <p>The note, written in the main hand, has been partly corrected by the same hand; six lines have been erased at the end.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small;">Fol. 12rb-va: Excerpt from the M&#228;&#7779;&#7717;af&#228; &#347;&#601;r&#705;at, Introductory rite of al-Mu&#705;allaqah.</span></p><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small;">Fol. 12rb: </span><span style="font-size: large;">&#4808;&#4843;&#4757;&#4709;&#4705;&#4961; &#4824;&#4757;&#4720;&#4961; &#4725;&#4773;&#4827;&#4824;&#4961; &#4773;&#4637;&#4677;&#4853;&#4632;&#4961; &#4768;&#4757;&#4709;&#4710;&#4961; &#4720;&#4768;&#4637;&#4653;&#4961; &#4704;&#4789;&#4617;&#4961; &#4773;&#4737;&#4853;&#4961; &#4808;&#4704;&#4789;&#4617;&#4961; &#4704;&#4819;&#4619;&#4722;&#4611;&#4961; &#4616;&#4773;&#4877;&#4829;&#4773;&#4725;&#4752;&#4961; &#4635;&#4653;&#4843;&#4637;&#4961; &#4808;&#4619;&#4850;&#4720;&#4961; &#4768;&#4637;&#4619;&#4781;&#4962; &#4776;&#4632;&#4961; &#4770;&#4845;&#4637;&#4656;&#4622;&#4633;&#4961; &#4616;&#4781;[&#4653;]&#4661;&#4722;&#4843;&#4757;&#4961; &#4672;&#4618;&#4616;&#4961; &#4656;&#4634;&#4819;&#4961; &#4720;&#4768;&#4637;&#4650;&#4611;&#4961; &#4616;&#4773;&#4877;&#4829;&#4773;&#4725;&#4752;&#4961; &#4635;&#4653;&#4843;&#4637;&#4961; &#4773;&#4661;&#4632;&#4961; &#4819;&#4706;&#4845;&#4961; &#4808;&#4781;&#4705;&#4653;&#4961;&#160;&#4813;&#4773;&#4721;&#4962; &#160;...</span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The initial line and the name of Mary are rubricated.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small;">Fol. 174rc: Donation note.</span></p><q xml:lang="gez"><p><span style="font-size: small;">Fol. 174rc:</span><span style="font-size:9.0pt;"> </span><span style="font-size: large;">&#4616;&#4827;&#4722;: &#4720;&#4768;&#4637;&#4653;&#4961; &#4768;&#4925;&#4624;&#4941;&#4781;&#4811;&#4961; &#4704;&#4757;&#4811;&#4845;&#4840;&#4962; &#4768;&#4752;&#4961; &#4808;&#4621;&#4848;&#4961; &#4768;&#4648;&#4875;&#4810;&#4961; &#4648;&#4853;&#4769;&#4961; &#4616;&#4768;&#4705;&#4752;&#4961; &#4635;&#4725;&#4843;&#4661;&#4962; &#4808;&#4808;&#4608;&#4709;&#4781;&#4811;&#4961; &#4616;&#4632;&#4677;&#4848;&#4656;&#4961; &#4768;&#4705;&#4840;&#4961; &#4768;&#4648;&#4875;&#4810;&#4961; &#4824;&#4848;&#4709;&#4648;&#4961; &#4851;&#4638;&#4962; &#4776;&#4632;&#4961; &#4725;&#4777;&#4752;&#4754;&#4961; &#4819;&#4651;&#4674;&#4720;&#4961; &#4637;&#4661;&#4616;&#4961; &#4768;&#4637;&#4619;&#4778;&#4840;&#4961; &#4740;&#4653;&#4962; &#4773;&#4637;&#4899;&#4752;&#4961; &#4768;&#4621;&#4709;&#4840;&#4961; &#4768;&#4624;&#4722;&#4961; &#4637;&#4877;&#4707;&#4648;&#4961; &#4640;&#4755;&#4845;&#4962; &#4616;&#4781;&#4633;&#4754;&#4961; &#4774;&#4768;&#4704;&#4813;&#4840;&#4961; &#4808;&#4768;&#4739;&#4813;&#4840;&#4961; &#4704;&#4773;&#4757;&#4720;&#4961; &#4773;&#4877;&#4829;&#4773;&#4725;&#4752;&#4961; &#4635;&#4653;&#4843;&#4637;&#4961; &#4773;&#4661;&#4773;&#4616;&#4781;&#4633;&#4961; &#4704;&#4941;&#4677;&#4653;&#4961; &#4632;&#4757;&#4936;&#4659;&#4810;&#4962; &#160;&#4776;&#4632;&#4961; &#4770;&#4725;&#4653;&#4661;&#4769;&#4754;&#4961; &#4704;&#4629;&#4845;&#4808;&#4725;&#4840;&#4961; &#4808;&#4704;&#4638;&#4725;&#4840;&#4962; &#4773;&#4661;&#4632;&#4961; &#4768;&#4621;&#4709;&#4840;&#4961; &#4824;&#4632;&#4853;&#4961; &#4824;&#4773;&#4757;&#4704;&#4620;&#4781;&#4633;&#4961; &#4808;&#4720;&#4768;&#4637;&#4649;&#4961; &#4768;&#4757;&#4725;&#4633;&#4961; &#4776;&#4632;&#4961; &#4840;&#4819;&#4706;&#4961; &#4773;&#4741;&#4813;&#4961; &#4632;&#4757;&#4936;&#4659;&#4810;&#4962; &#4773;&#4637;&#4752;&#4961; &#4773;&#4741;&#4813;&#4961; &#4645;&#4875;&#4810;&#4962; </span></p></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The note is written in the main hand, in red ink. It states that Wäldä ʾArägawi, disciple of ʾabunä Matǝyas, donated the Ms. to Däbrä Dammo. He pleads with the fathers and brothers not to forget him during his life and death because he does not have relatives to ask for.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title ተአምረ፡ ማርያም and the internal number of the monastic library (338) are written on fol. 1r together with two short notes: ዝተአምር፡ ዘደብረ፡ ዳሞ፡ መካነ፡ አቡነ፡ አረጋዊ፡ "This is the (book of) miracles of Däbrä Dammo, the place of ʾabunä ʾArägawi" and ተአምር፡ ዘእግዝእትነ፡ ማርየም "Miracles of Our Lady Mary".&#xD;
- Musical notation: fols. 11rb-12rb.&#xD;
- A secondary hand has added to some supplication: ወምስለ፡ ኵልነ፡ አግብርቲሃ "and with all of us, her servants" (fols. 18ra, 19vb, 29rc, 58va) or ወምስሌነሂ "and also with us" (fols. 20vc, 23va).&#xD;
&#xD;
- Erasures are marked with thin lines: e.g., fols. 9vb, 25rb, 49ra, 51vb, 57rc, 67ra, 76ra, 90vc, 93rc, 110vb, 112vc, 113rab, 117rc, 120rb, 124vab, 149rb, 154rb, 161va, 162rb, 170vb, 173vc. &#xD;
- Thin lines are used to fill the line: fols. 65rb, 68vb, 69rc, 92ra-vc, 158ra (at the end of several lines).&#xD;
- Omissions are inserted interlineally: fols. 9ra, 10va, 43ra, 53vc, 55vb, 57rc, 57vb, 70ra, 71rc, 72rc, 92rc, 93rc, 114va, 120rb, 120va, 126vc, 129va, 132rb, 142vb, 143vb, 148rb (in red), 152va, 159rb (in red), 160ra, 163vc.&#xD;
- Omitted incipit of one miracle is written in the upper margin on fol. 90r.&#xD;
- Corrections are written over erasures: fols. 112vb, 170rc.&#xD;
- Pen trial, mentioning Tuesday: fol. 177v.</item>
